ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class ChangeSysStatFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.ChangeSysStatFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ChangeSysStatFilter
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable

    Changes the system status filter options for a current system registration. This service used by the computing function to change the filter options for a current system registration.

    ChangeSysStatFilter Parameters
    sysStatRegisterID Mandatory Specifies the system registration identifier for the registration in which the filter is being changed.
    requestedStatusFilter Conditional Specifies the set of System Status Types that will be filtered (not sent) by the switching function. The only supported System Status Types are Normal and Disabled, and their values can be true (filtered) or false (sent). All other System Status Types default to true (filtered).

    Note that the ChangeSysStatFilterPrivateData object has an invertFilter parameter. When this invertFilter is set to true, the sense of the requestedStatusFilter is reversed. For example: usually, setting the Normal type to false and the Disabled type to true would result in the application receiving Normal System Status events, but Disabled events would be filtered. However, if the invertFilter is set to true, then the application would receive Disabled events. but Normal events would be filtered.

    CSTA Functional Requirements:

    1. The requestedStatusFilter parameter allows the computing function to choose the System Status Types for which no SystemStatus service requests should be issued by the switching function. This parameter only applies to the System Status service. If the System Status service has not been requested for this system registration, then the switching function will send a negative acknowledgement to the Change System Status Filter service request.
    2. An implementation that does not support all System Status Types will nevertheless accept the Change System Status Filter service even if the requested filter cannot be provided. The service acknowledgement indicates the actual set of System Status Types that will be filtered. This means that the actual set of filtered types returned in the positive acknowledgement may include additional types to be filtered (or fewer types generated by the switching function) than those requested in the service request.
